 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-2: Store::apply_tx — incremental mutation with index + view update (INV-STORE-001, ADR-STORE-005, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: Store is currently immutable. from_datoms() rebuilds 5 indexes + schema in O(n). The daemon needs O(k) in-place mutation. APPROACH: (1) Add pub fn apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) to Store. For each datom d: (a) self.datoms.insert(d.clone()) — canonical BTreeSet. (b) self.entity_index.entry(d.entity).or_default().push(d.clone()). (c) self.attribute_index.entry(d.attribute.clone()).or_default().push(d.clone()). (d) If let Value::Ref(target) = d.value: self.vaet_index.entry(target).or_default().push(d.clone()). (e) If d.op == Op::Assert: self.avet_index.entry((d.attribute.clone(), d.value.clone())).or_default().push(d.clone()). (f) live_view update: if d.op == Assert, check if d.tx > existing live_view[(d.entity, d.attribute)].1 — if so, update. If d.op == Retract, remove live_view entry if value matches, then scan entity_datoms for next-latest Assert to restore. (g) self.views.observe(&d, &self.schema) — update materialized views. (2) Frontier update: for each unique agent in datoms, advance frontier if tx is newer. (3) Schema update: if any datom.attribute starts with ':db/', call Schema::from_datoms on full datom set (rare, O(n) acceptable). (4) ISOMORPHISM: S.clone().apply_tx(D) == Store::from_datoms(S.datom_set() union D) — fundamental correctness property. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Isomorphism property test: 100 proptest iterations, random stores (up to 1000 datoms) and random transactions (up to 50 datoms). (B) O(k) complexity: apply_tx(10 datoms) takes < 1ms regardless of store size (1K/10K/100K). (C) All 5 indexes consistent after apply_tx. (D) live_view correct after Assert and Retract sequences. (E) Frontier monotonically advances. (F) Schema updated on :db/* attributes. (G) MaterializedViews updated correctly (fitness matches batch). DEPENDS-ON: CE-1 (t-2d4db20a). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-001, ADR-STORE-005."
